-- U.S. Mutual Funds Drew $3.81 Billion in Deposits, ICI Says
-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 2012-08-01T19:28:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/u-s-mutual-funds-drew-3-81-billion-in-deposits-ici-says.html
 U.S. mutual funds attracted
$3.81 billion last week as investors added money to fixed-income
and continued withdrawals from equities.  Taxable bond funds had deposits of $4.29 billion and
municipal bond funds gathered $1.47 billion in the week ended
July 25, according to the Washington-based Investment Company
Institute. Funds that buy U.S. stocks had redemptions of $2.13
billion, while those that invest in international equities had
redemptions of $568 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Charles Stein  in Boston at 
